g.text: Alice: "Great, I'll give it to your colleagues. You don't have to worry about the case anymore, we'll send our officers to take away the body."
You: "There might be a *sequence killer* on the loose."
Perception (Hearing): You can hear her quickly typing in the background.
You: "An unidentified middle-aged man. Looks like he slipped, fell through a hole in the boardwalk and hit his head against the metal bench."
Alice: "Did you perform a field autopsy?"
You: "No, it's still just a theory."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We suspect he might have been inebriated when he fell -- there were bottles all around him, and traces of vomit on his shirt."
Alice: "I have assigned the case to Lieutenant Kim Kitsuragi. Please follow up on this library lead to identify the man. We'll send someone to take the body to the morgue."
Alice: "What about his belongings? Did you examine his clothes?"
You: "It's from Central Jamrock Public Library. It belongs to someone named Billie MÃ©jean."
Alice: "A sequence killer." You can hear her stop typing. "Are you suggesting that this might be connected to the case you're working on?"
Alice: "Can you please describe the body -- age, sex, cause of death?"
Alice: "No field autopsy necessary..." she repeats.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Assign it to someone else, Alice -- we've got enough on our plate."
You: "He was wearing boots, trousers and an old leather jacket with a bright blue lining. I found a library card from his pockets."
You: "Please assign it to someone else."
Alice: "That's all for now. Thank you for reporting in. Is there anything else I can do for you?"
Alice: "What about his belongings? Did you examine his clothes?" She goes on as if nothing happened.
Alice: "I see." Silence. "This is something you should discuss with the Lieutenant Kitsuragi, as you're sharing the case."
Alice: You can hear her sigh audibly on the other side.
Kim Kitsuragi: "It looked like an accident to me, Alice," the lieutenant rushes in to say. "But that's for the guys in processing to confirm."
You: "An unidentified middle-aged man. Height 170-175 cm, dark hair, medium build. Looks like he slipped, fell through a hole in the boardwalk and hit his head against the metal bench."
You: "No, seems like it was an accident."
Alice: "That's all for now. Thank you for reporting in. Is there anything else I can do for you?"

Kim Kitsuragi: "The man was about 173 cm tall, stout, with dark hair and a moustache. We suspect he might have been inebriated when he slipped -- there were bottles all around him, and traces of vomit on his shirt."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, we're not," the lieutenant rushes in to say. "There is no evidence to suggest that this man was connected to the lynching -- or that we're dealing with a sequence killer here."
Alice: "You just made it up?" Silence. "I see."
Alice: "No? It's some *other* sequence killer?" Silence. "I see."
Alice: "Any information on the library card?"
Alice: "Do you and Lieutenant Kitsuragi want to take the case or should I assign it to someone else?"
Authority: So unprofessional of you... Pity!
Kim Kitsuragi: "It looked like a simple accident to me, Alice. No field autopsy necessary."
Alice: "One moment..." You can hear her shuffling through some papers.
You: "Actually, scratch that -- there is no sequence killer, I just made it up."
